<refentry>
  <refnamediv id="minAggregate">
    <refname>min</refname>

    <refpurpose>Minimum value aggregate</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <synopsis>AQL% <command>SELECT</command> min(<replaceable>attribute</replaceable>) <command>FROM</command> <replaceable>array</replaceable>;</synopsis>

    <synopsis>AFL% aggregate(<replaceable>array</replaceable>,min(<replaceable>attribute</replaceable>)<optional>,<replaceable>dimension_1</replaceable>,<replaceable>dimension_2</replaceable>,...</optional></synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Summary</title>

    <para><indexterm>
        <primary>min</primary>
      </indexterm><indexterm>
        <primary>aggregates</primary>

        <secondary>min</secondary>
      </indexterm>The min aggregate takes a set of scalar values from an array
    attribute and returns the minimum value.</para>

    <para>The minimum value of an empty set is NULL. The min of a set that
    contains only NULL values is also NULL. If the set contains NULL and NOT
    NULL values, the min aggregate considers only NOT NULL values.</para>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Example</title>

    <informalexample>
      <para>This example finds the minimum of every column of a 3<symbol
      role="symbolfont">×</symbol>3 array.</para>

      <procedure>
        <step>
          <para>Create an array:<programlisting>CREATE ARRAY m3x3&lt;val:double&gt;[i=0:2,3,0,j=0:2,3,0];</programlisting></para>
        </step>

        <step>
          <para>Put values of 0–8 into m3x3:<programlisting>store(build(m3x3,i*3+j),m3x3);</programlisting><screen>[
[(0),(1),(2)],
[(3),(4),(5)],
[(6),(7),(8)]
]</screen></para>
        </step>

        <step>
          <para>Find the minimum value of every column of
          m3x3:<programlisting>aggregate(m3x3,min(val),j);</programlisting>This
          query returns:<screen>[(0),(1),(2)]</screen></para>
        </step>
      </procedure>
    </informalexample>
  </refsect1>
</refentry>
